Pre-merge code review. New RichAsyncFunction below — calls a downstream gRPC service. We've had leak issues before so the team wants a careful review. Does this code have leak risk?

```java
public class EnrichmentAsyncFn extends RichAsyncFunction<Event, Enriched> {
    private transient ManagedChannel channel;
    private transient EnrichServiceGrpc.EnrichServiceFutureStub stub;

    @Override
    public void open(Configuration parameters) {
        channel = ManagedChannelBuilder.forAddress("enrich-svc:50051", 50051)
            .usePlaintext()
            .build();
        stub = EnrichServiceGrpc.newFutureStub(channel);
    }

    @Override
    public void asyncInvoke(Event in, ResultFuture<Enriched> rf) {
        ListenableFuture<EnrichReply> reply = stub.enrich(toRequest(in));
        Futures.addCallback(reply, new FutureCallback<>() {
            @Override public void onSuccess(EnrichReply r) {
                rf.complete(List.of(fromReply(r)));
            }
            @Override public void onFailure(Throwable t) {
                rf.completeExceptionally(t);
            }
        }, MoreExecutors.directExecutor());
    }

    @Override
    public void close() throws Exception {
        if (channel != null) channel.shutdown();
        super.close();
    }
}
